Note that ommiting the `unsafe_destructor` and not storing the pointer to `A` does compile too:

``` rust
struct A;

struct B<'a>;

impl<'a> Drop for B<'a> {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
    }
}

fn main() {
}
```
